<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>530 and DT-466/408 Diesel Engine Service (1994) - VIBRATION DAMPER, CRANKSHAFT, MAIN BEARINGS, FLYWHEEL AND
        CRANKCASE - INSTALLATION - VIBRATION DAMPER
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="2">
        <title>VIBRATION DAMPER</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the vibration damper as follows:</para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Place damper directly on a hot plate. Mark damper with a thermomelt crayon 388&#176; F
                    (198&#176; C) and heat. When crayon melts,
                    <emph type="bold">using welding gloves</emph>, install damper on crankshaft nose. Be sure that
                    keyway on damper aligns with key on crankshaft.
                    <emph type="bold">DO NOT</emph>
                    install damper when cold (room temperature).
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Install damper retainer using correct bolts. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050764">7.64</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Prevent crankshaft from turning and tighten bolts to special torque value. Refer to
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1050764">7.64</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    .
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1050763" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg3589" filename="../figeg3/eg3589.png" type="png"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.63.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Crankcase</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Mounting Bar (2)</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Oil Pan</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1050764" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg2402" filename="../figeg2/eg2402.png" type="png"/>
                    <caption>Figure 7.64.</caption>
                    <calloutgroup>
                        <callout1>1. Vibration Damper</callout1>
                        <callout1>2. Retainer Mounting Bolt</callout1>
                        <callout1>3. Retainer</callout1>
                        <callout1>4. Front Cover</callout1>
                        <callout1>5. RTV Bead</callout1>
                    </calloutgroup>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
